This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it proposes a new method for improving network performance in image super resolution reconstruction task. It also involves the use of Inception Model, which is commonly used in computer vision tasks. 

It is also likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories as it involves the use of random forest and explores the relationship between tree structure and network performance. 

The neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category is also a possibility as the paper proposes a new network architecture. 

Finally, the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category may also be relevant as the paper involves the use of a tree structure to reduce network parameters.
